abstract: The Akron (Ohio) papers announce the death by accident, of JAMES BROWN, a notorious counterfeiter, who resided in that portion of the State for a number of years. abstract: BENJAMIN B. MARSCHALL and AUGUST FRICE, recently convicted of the murder of a German named FORSTER, at Boyd Hill, near this city, a short time since, were executed to-day. abstract: Another ice-boat race came off here to-day. The distance sailed was sixteen miles and return, the boats going to Newburgh. The Una arrived at Newburgh ahead on the down trip and came in ahead on her return. abstract: BABCOCK.--In Brooklyn, on Seventh Day, First Month, 26th, at the residence of her brother, Heary Babcock, ELIZABETH BABCOCK, aged 69 years. abstract: Advices from Yreka say that the weather up the coast during the past fortnight has been the most severe ever known. The snow on Scott Mountain is from twelve to fifteen feet deep. Communication with Washington Territory over the mountains is nearly broken off. and the telegraph line in the Territory is almost totally destroyed.
